Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The house stood on a slight rise just on the edge of the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.00,0:00:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It stood on its own and looked out over a broad spread of west country farmland.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.00,0:00:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a remarkable house by any means.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.24,0:00:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about thirty years old, squatish, squarish, made of brick, and had four windows set in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.92,0:00:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the front of a size and proportion which more or less exactly failed to please the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.60,0:00:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.10,0:00:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The only person for whom the house was in any way special was Arthur Dent, and that was only
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.22,0:00:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because it happened to be the one he lived in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.14,0:00:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He had lived in it for about three years, ever since he had moved out of London because it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.90,0:00:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,made him nervous and irritable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.62,0:00:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about thirty as well, tall, dark-haired, and never quite at ease with himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.22,0:00:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that used to worry him most was the fact that people always used to ask him
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.10,0:00:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what he was looking so worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.74,0:01:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He worked in local radio, which he always used to tell his friends was a lot more interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.56,0:01:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,than they probably thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of his friends worked in advertising.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.94,0:01:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,On Wednesday night it had rained very heavily.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.38,0:01:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The lane was wet and muddy, but the Thursday morning sun was bright and clear as it shone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.46,0:01:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,on Arthur Dent's house for what was to be the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.22,0:01:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It hadn't properly registered yet with Arthur that the council wanted to knock it down and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.66,0:01:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,build a bypass instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.26,0:01:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At eight o'clock on Thursday morning, Arthur didn't feel very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.12,0:01:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He woke up blearily, got up, wandered blearily round his room, opened a window, saw a bulldozer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.14,0:01:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,found his slippers, and stomped off to the bathroom to wash.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.50,0:01:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Toothpaste on the brush, so scrub.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.26,0:01:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaving mirror, pointing at the ceiling, he adjusted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.78,0:02:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For a moment it reflected a second bulldozer through the bathroom window.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.86,0:02:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Properly adjusted, it reflected Arthur Dent's bristles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He shaved them off, washed, dried, and stomped off to the kitchen to find something pleasant
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.60,0:02:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to put in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.50,0:02:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Kettle, plug, fridge, milk, coffee, yawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.90,0:02:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The word bulldozer wandered through his mind for a moment in search of something to connect
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.98,0:02:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.34,0:02:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The bulldozer outside the kitchen window was quite a big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.46,0:02:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He stared at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.66,0:02:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yellow, he thought, and stomped off back to his bedroom to get dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,During the bathroom, he stopped to drink a large glass of water, and another.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.72,0:02:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He began to suspect that he was hungover.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.98,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was he hungover?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.78,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Had he been drinking the night before?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He supposed that he must have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.70,0:03:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He caught a glint in the shaving mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.50,0:03:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yellow, he thought, and stomped onto the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.46,0:03:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood and thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.94,0:03:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The pub, he thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.14,0:03:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear, the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.22,0:03:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He vaguely remembered being angry, angry about something that seemed important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd been telling people about it, telling people about it at great lengths, he rather
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.76,0:03:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,His clearest visual recollection was of glazed looks on other people's faces, something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.70,0:03:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,about a new bypass he'd just found out about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.70,0:03:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It had been in the pipeline for months, only no one seemed to have known about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.18,0:03:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He took a swig of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.34,0:03:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It would sort itself out, he decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.14,0:03:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No one wanted a bypass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.02,0:03:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The council didn't have a leg to stand on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.46,0:03:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It would sort itself out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.42,0:03:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,God, what a terrible hangover it had earned him, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.18,0:03:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at himself in the wardrobe mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:03:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He stuck out his tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.86,0:04:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yellow, he thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.82,0:04:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The word yellow wandered through his mind in search of something to connect with.
